@NODE What_is_itb " What is M-BatchFS"

M-BatchFS is a tagged file list manager for DLG.  M-BatchFS allows users to
delete tagged files from their list by using numbers.

    o Uses the same key's to move pointer as M-TagFS.
    o Doesn't delete the entries until the user exits.
    o Correctly handles the .CDL file.

@ENDNODE

@NODE CPS " How CPS rates are calculated."

Characters per second rates are calculated differently for low speed and high
speed modems.  For low speed modems this calculation is used:

   cps = baud x 0.095  ==> 2400 x 0.095 = 228 cps

for high speed modems:

   cps = baud x 0.109  ==> 9600 x 0.109 = 1046 cps

@ENDNODE

@NODE Setting_upb " Setting up M-BatchFS"

To set up M-BatchFS, simply add a menu item to the files menu using Overlay
and all other defaults.  Set to executable and call M-BatchFS thus:

  DLGConfig:Master/M-BatchFS [-R]

The -R switch will reverse the tag status.  Usually the files show up as
reverse video when they are tagged for removal.  With this option, the files
will show in reverse video until they are marked for deletion.

Copy the help file into the appropriate menu directory.  Installation is now
complete.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Historyb " M-BatchFS history"

Version 1.0  - Initial release.

Version 1.1  - Fixed a problem with checking for existing files.
             - Removed M-BatchFS keyfile detection. Now ONLY checks for
               M-TagFS.KEY to unlock it.

Version 1.2  - Added -R switch.

Version 2.0  - Added .CDL support.
             - Fixed a severe bug when more than 255 files tagged.

Version 2.0c - Removed 4 enforcer hits.
             - Now runs M-Support to update files before killing batch list.

Version 2.1  - If registered, only displays the program ID on most occasions.
               The 'registered to' banner will appear randomly upon exit.
             - Fixed a MAJOR bug which caused system crashes on rare
               occasions, and only from remote ports.

Version 2.2  - Now accepts comma as seperator when inputing file numbers.

Version 3.0  - A few minor optimisations.

@ENDNODE

